# Test Plan

## Purpose

Summarize what DM3b will build and what DM3c will run. Name the
documents this plan traces back to:

- `docs/spec.md`
- `docs/targets.md`
- `docs/testbench.md`
- `docs/analysis/decomposition.md`
- `docs/analysis/pipeline-mapping.md`
- `docs/analysis/data-movement.md`

## Testbench Architecture

Describe the UVM-lite topology DM3b will implement. Cover, at a
minimum:

- Each Sequencer (one per stimulus class) -- name, payload type,
  what it generates.
- Each Driver (one per external interface) -- name, target port,
  handshake protocol.
- Each Monitor (one per observable signal / port) -- name,
  observed port, which Scoreboard(s) it feeds.
- Each Scoreboard (one per correctness invariant) -- name,
  invariant in plain English, monitor inputs, comparison
  strategy.
- The `SimEnvBuilder` wiring helper that returns a fully
  assembled `SimEnv`.

## Implementation Baseline

Inherit `docs/testbench.md`'s `## Implementation Baseline`:

- **Baseline**: `lib:examples/<NN-name>/test/`
- DM3b copies the baseline's file structure as a starting point.

## Testbench Implementation Milestones (DM3b)

Walk these in order. DM3b stops for a paired critique after each.

1. [Milestone 01: Payloads and Sequencers](./tb-milestone-01-payloads-and-sequencers.md)
2. [Milestone 02: Drivers](./tb-milestone-02-drivers.md)
3. [Milestone 03: Monitors](./tb-milestone-03-monitors.md)
4. [Milestone 04: Scoreboards](./tb-milestone-04-scoreboards.md)
5. [Milestone 05: SimEnv and Smoke](./tb-milestone-05-simenv-and-smoke.md)

Replace, merge, split, or drop milestones only when justified by
the design (e.g. no Scoreboard invariants -> merge 04 into 05);
document the rationale here. Each file holds at most 10 tasks.

## Test Execution Milestones (DM3c)

Walk these in order. DM3c stops for a paired critique after each.
The four canonical categories (smoke, edge, stress, random) are
each required and each maps to ONE OR MORE consecutive milestones;
the coverage milestone closes the step. A milestone file covers
exactly one category -- never mix.

1. [Milestone 01: Smoke](./test-milestone-01-smoke.md)
2. [Milestone 02: Edge](./test-milestone-02-edge.md)
3. [Milestone 03: Stress](./test-milestone-03-stress.md)
4. [Milestone 04: Random](./test-milestone-04-random.md)
5. [Milestone 05: Coverage](./test-milestone-05-coverage.md)

When a category exceeds the 10-task cap, split it with a letter
suffix on NN and an axis tag (e.g.
`test-milestone-02a-edge-arithmetic.md`,
`test-milestone-02b-edge-flow-control.md`). Letters contiguous
from `a`. All splits for a category walk before the next category
begins.

Categories that are genuinely N/A for this design (e.g. smoke for
a combinational design with no flow-control) still get a milestone
file -- with an explicit `RESOLVED:` line inside explaining the
omission. Don't silently skip a category.

## Traceability

Map every spec requirement / target / decomposition operation to a
specific task in a specific milestone file.

| Spec requirement | Milestone file :: task |
| --- | --- |
| `<quote requirement>` | `<milestone-file>::<task>` |

| Target row | Milestone file :: task |
| --- | --- |
| `<target>` | `test-milestone-03-stress.md::<task>` |

| Decomposition operation | Milestone file :: task |
| --- | --- |
| `<operation>` | `<milestone-file>::<task>` |

## Coverage

Strategy lives in [`coverage.md`](./coverage.md). DM3c writes the
measured percentage and report path here once the coverage
milestone runs:

- Coverage report:
  `<path>` (line: `<percentage>`%)
- Run command: see `coverage.md`.

## Notes

- DM3b walks `tb-milestone-NN-*.md` one at a time, stopping for a
  critique after each milestone. Final tb-milestone owns the
  basic data-flow smoke test.
- DM3c walks `test-milestone-NN-*.md` one at a time, stopping for
  a critique after each. Final test-milestone runs
  `cargo-llvm-cov` and records the coverage outcome above.
- No file may carry more than 10 `- [ ]` rows
  (`docs/plan-management.md` enforces the cap).
